title: For Sale/Trade:  H&K USP .45
postcontent: H&K USP .45. Made 2009 according to "AK" date code on slide. Police surplus, formerly property of the New Smyrna Beach Police Department, and appropriately marked in unobtrusive lettering along the slide. I discussed the history of this gun by e-mail with a firearms quartermaster of that department and he told me that their PD replaced the S&W 4506 with these H&Ks and then the H&K with the Glock 35 .40 caliber -- seems to me a step down in terms of firepower but I didn't say so. As you can hopefully see by the pictures, this is one of the least used pieces of police surplus I've seen. I suspect it was probably issued to someone with a desk job who didn't feel the need to slip it into or out of a holster very often and also didn't spend much time at the range, or maybe it was just issued to an officer who took special care of his weapon.The USP comes in several different trigger styles. This is the default Type 1 style with a traditional DA/SA trigger and safety that can allow you to carry decocked with the safety on, decocked with the safety off, or cocked and locked in the style of a 1911, while also functioning as a decocker when pressed fully downward.Comes with original box, three magazines, and factory night sights that still work, though I don't know how many years they have left in them. It's seven years old, so I suspect if you can find out how long these sights are meant to last you can get a pretty good idea. I will also include a Streamlight TLR-4 with an adapter to fit the proprietary H&K rail. A pretty solid value all in all, I think.
